                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.51/1255: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-23T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 23, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>225. My telegram No. 220, September 16, 4 p.m. and Department’s telegram No. 162,
                    September 19, 4 p.m. Pessimistic observations of some Chilean officials to
                    Commercial Attaché<note n="31" xml:id="d819fn1">Clarence C. Brooks.</note>
                    apparently due to the failure of Chilean representatives in Washington to keep
                    them properly informed. They are gratified at bank’s prompt action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
